1
00:00:12,840 --> 00:00:13,560
Big...

2
00:00:13,760 --> 00:00:14,840
Who wants... wants something to eat?

3
00:00:15,280 --> 00:00:16,800
Qiang... Qiang...

4
00:00:18,840 --> 00:00:19,920
The guy ran away.

5
00:00:20,560 --> 00:00:21,360
He really gave it to me.

6
00:00:22,520 --> 00:00:23,360
This is too valuable.

7
00:00:23,480 --> 00:00:24,640
We can't keep it. We must return it.

8
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:25,840
Stop! Don't run!

9
00:00:26,040 --> 00:00:27,760
Stop! Stop!

10
00:00:27,760 --> 00:00:29,560
Don't run! Don't run!

11
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:30,520
Stop!

12
00:00:31,200 --> 00:00:32,440
Don't run!

13
00:00:32,440 --> 00:00:33,240
Stop! Don't run!

14
00:00:33,640 --> 00:00:34,440
Stop!

15
00:00:35,080 --> 00:00:35,640
Stop!

16
00:00:35,640 --> 00:00:37,800
Don't run! Stop!

17
00:00:39,120 --> 00:00:39,920
Hello, Sister-in-law.

18
00:00:40,360 --> 00:00:41,000
Come back!

19
00:00:42,360 --> 00:00:42,760
Sister-in-law.

20
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:44,120
I have something to do.

21
00:00:44,280 --> 00:00:45,280
What are you doing with the flowers?

22
00:00:45,640 --> 00:00:46,400
I...

23
00:00:47,120 --> 00:00:48,720
I'm giving... giving...

24
00:00:49,760 --> 00:00:50,720
Giving... giving them to Big Brother.

25
00:00:51,120 --> 00:00:52,480
Your Big Brother likes these?

26
00:00:52,640 --> 00:00:53,520
He doesn't like them anymore.

27
00:00:54,760 --> 00:00:55,640
Sit down.

28
00:00:56,120 --> 00:00:56,840
Sit.

29
00:00:58,200 --> 00:00:58,760
Alright.

30
00:00:59,920 --> 00:01:00,640
What's wrong?

31
00:01:01,800 --> 00:01:03,040
Your Big Brother lately...

32
00:01:03,040 --> 00:01:04,200
...keeps avoiding me.

33
00:01:04,680 --> 00:01:05,920
Do you know why?

34
00:01:06,360 --> 00:01:07,360
He's avoiding you?

35
00:01:07,440 --> 00:01:08,360
How is that possible?

36
00:01:08,800 --> 00:01:09,760
Then tell me...

37
00:01:09,760 --> 00:01:11,040
...how is he avoiding you?

38
00:01:11,640 --> 00:01:12,200
Well...

39
00:01:12,360 --> 00:01:13,240
As soon as I draw my sword...

40
00:01:13,240 --> 00:01:14,320
...he runs away.

41
00:01:14,920 --> 00:01:15,920
Is he such a wimp?

42
00:01:15,920 --> 00:01:16,920
How could he be a wimp?

43
00:01:17,520 --> 00:01:18,960
My Big Brother loves fighting battles.

44
00:01:20,040 --> 00:01:20,760
Back in the day...

45
00:01:20,760 --> 00:01:22,240
...someone raided our camp at night.

46
00:01:22,240 --> 00:01:22,960
Without a word...

47
00:01:22,960 --> 00:01:24,640
...he took his sword and charged into the enemy ranks.

48
00:01:24,960 --> 00:01:26,480
Like a descended deity...

49
00:01:26,880 --> 00:01:27,960
...he fought in the enemy formation and...

50
00:01:27,960 --> 00:01:29,200
...carved a path through their ranks.

51
00:01:29,640 --> 00:01:31,880
Taking enemy heads was a piece of cake.

52
00:01:32,160 --> 00:01:33,040
How could he be a wimp?

53
00:01:33,480 --> 00:01:34,480
Really?

54
00:01:34,880 --> 00:01:35,640
He's that amazing?

55
00:01:35,640 --> 00:01:36,600
Of course.

56
00:01:36,680 --> 00:01:38,320
He's been bragging about this for ten years.

57
00:01:39,040 --> 00:01:39,480
But...

58
00:01:40,240 --> 00:01:41,360
...don't tell him I told you.

59
00:01:41,920 --> 00:01:42,640
The truth is...

60
00:01:42,640 --> 00:01:43,960
...it's because he rushed out in such a hurry...

61
00:01:43,960 --> 00:01:44,760
...he wasn't wearing pants.

62
00:01:44,760 --> 00:01:45,920
It scared the enemy stiff.

63
00:01:46,520 --> 00:01:48,520
So naturally, they stood still and let him kill them.

64
00:01:48,920 --> 00:01:50,080
No wonder.

65
00:01:50,080 --> 00:01:51,280
I knew it.

66
00:01:51,760 --> 00:01:52,320
Sister-in-law...

67
00:01:52,320 --> 00:01:54,960
Actually, my Big Brother really likes you.

68
00:01:55,680 --> 00:01:56,800
Just yesterday he asked me...

69
00:01:56,800 --> 00:01:58,320
...what gift he should give you.

70
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:03,640
Maybe it's because

71
00:02:04,320 --> 00:02:05,960
I haven't cleared my name yet.

72
00:02:07,360 --> 00:02:08,320
Anyway, no matter what,

73
00:02:08,320 --> 00:02:08,880
Sister-in-law,

74
00:02:09,080 --> 00:02:10,080
I believe in you.

75
00:02:11,600 --> 00:02:12,760
Don't run! Stop!

76
00:02:12,880 --> 00:02:13,440
Catch him!

77
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:14,240
Don't run!

78
00:02:14,240 --> 00:02:16,120
Stop!

79
00:02:16,120 --> 00:02:17,520
Don't run!

80
00:02:17,520 --> 00:02:18,520
Stop! Don't run!

81
00:02:18,960 --> 00:02:20,000
What's going on here?

82
00:02:21,480 --> 00:02:23,360
Is the village holding a sports meet?

83
00:02:24,240 --> 00:02:25,440
There are quite a few events.

84
00:02:28,240 --> 00:02:29,440
Isn't this He Qi's blade?

85
00:02:30,640 --> 00:02:32,160
It's great that you know him.

86
00:02:32,520 --> 00:02:33,600
I mobilized the villagers

87
00:02:33,600 --> 00:02:35,200
to look for him, but we couldn't find him.

88
00:02:35,360 --> 00:02:36,160
What happened?

89
00:02:36,440 --> 00:02:37,560
It was so pitiful.

90
00:02:37,640 --> 00:02:39,240
He looked unkempt and dirty.

91
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:40,000
It looked like

92
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:41,160
he hadn't eaten for days.

93
00:02:41,360 --> 00:02:43,080
I'll ask someone to prepare some food for them.

94
00:02:43,160 --> 00:02:43,880
And he ran away.

95
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:45,360
No need to pity them.

96
00:02:45,360 --> 00:02:46,480
They are enemy spies.

97
00:02:46,760 --> 00:02:48,200
They've done so many terrible things.

98
00:02:48,200 --> 00:02:48,600
Exactly.

99
00:02:48,600 --> 00:02:50,360
I think they were quite polite.

100
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:51,320
Their style wasn't bad either.

101
00:02:51,320 --> 00:02:52,920
They even gave such a precious gift.

102
00:02:53,520 --> 00:02:55,080
You guys are too saintly.

103
00:02:55,480 --> 00:02:56,360
From now on, your village

104
00:02:56,560 --> 00:02:57,640
should be called Saintly Village.

105
00:02:58,520 --> 00:02:59,400
Saintly Village.

106
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:00,880
That's a nice name.

107
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:02,960
It fits our village's character.

108
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:04,280
Being kind to others,

109
00:03:04,560 --> 00:03:05,400
treating people with sincerity.

110
00:03:05,960 --> 00:03:07,160
Thank you for the name, Miss.

111
00:03:07,840 --> 00:03:08,640
From now on, our village

112
00:03:08,760 --> 00:03:09,640
will be called Saintly Village.

113
00:03:09,640 --> 00:03:10,080
Good, good, good.

114
00:03:11,160 --> 00:03:12,720
Then this old man will take his leave.

115
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:14,560
Excuse me.

116
00:03:14,680 --> 00:03:15,440
Saintly Village.

117
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:16,320
Awesome.

118
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:18,600
Can't the village chief tell sarcasm?

119
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:20,360
He's quite kind.

120
00:03:20,360 --> 00:03:21,040
Yes, yes.

121
00:03:22,520 --> 00:03:23,600
One more thing.

122
00:03:23,920 --> 00:03:25,240
If you run into him later,

123
00:03:25,240 --> 00:03:25,920
tell him that

124
00:03:26,120 --> 00:03:27,320
living on the mountain is inconvenient.

125
00:03:27,320 --> 00:03:28,200
If he's not used to it,

126
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:29,120
he can come down.

127
00:03:29,880 --> 00:03:30,720
You know that

128
00:03:30,720 --> 00:03:31,680
our villagers

129
00:03:31,680 --> 00:03:32,640
are very hospitable.

130
00:03:32,880 --> 00:03:34,400
You also know our village rules,

131
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:35,520
hitting people is not allowed.

132
00:03:40,840 --> 00:03:42,360
We have to think of a way.

133
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:43,920
With them living here,

134
00:03:43,920 --> 00:03:44,960
it doesn't feel safe.

135
00:03:44,960 --> 00:03:46,280
That's for sure.

136
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:47,600
Let's find the vat first.

137
00:03:47,920 --> 00:03:49,800
It'll be trouble if they find it first.

138
00:03:49,960 --> 00:03:51,240
Never doing anything productive.

139
00:03:52,920 --> 00:03:53,960
What an attitude.

140
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:54,800
Tsk.

141
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:56,600
What should we do?

142
00:03:56,840 --> 00:03:57,600
Brother Yuwen,

143
00:03:58,440 --> 00:04:00,240
I traded for a cabinet with a villager.

144
00:04:00,520 --> 00:04:01,880
Can you help me pick it up?

145
00:04:02,160 --> 00:04:03,440
Why did you trade for a cabinet?

146
00:04:04,160 --> 00:04:04,960
Because...

147
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:07,080
I don't know how long we'll stay here.

148
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:08,680
So I thought

149
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:09,880
I'd make this home

150
00:04:10,040 --> 00:04:11,360
look nice and pretty.

151
00:04:11,600 --> 00:04:12,160
This...

152
00:04:14,080 --> 00:04:14,920
Home?

153
00:04:17,400 --> 00:04:18,520
Let's go, let's get the cabinet.

154
00:04:19,280 --> 00:04:20,360
You should have said so earlier.

155
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:20,840
Look at you,

156
00:04:20,840 --> 00:04:22,280
wanting to fix up our... our home.

157
00:04:22,280 --> 00:04:22,920
You mentioned a cabinet...

158
00:04:23,360 --> 00:04:24,080
We were talking business.

159
00:04:24,080 --> 00:04:25,160
What is going on?

160
00:04:30,720 --> 00:04:31,520
Miss Aqin,

161
00:04:32,280 --> 00:04:33,600
should we build a cabinet?

162
00:04:33,920 --> 00:04:34,720
No way.

163
00:04:35,520 --> 00:04:36,720
We could build a daybed too.

164
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:37,840
What do you like?

165
00:04:37,840 --> 00:04:38,840
We can build whatever, okay?

166
00:04:51,240 --> 00:04:52,040
What are you doing?

167
00:04:55,480 --> 00:04:56,280
What is that?

168
00:05:00,160 --> 00:05:01,800
I learned it from the villagers.

169
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:04,280
I wanted to embroider you in battle.

170
00:05:04,520 --> 00:05:05,360
Let me see.

171
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:08,400
It looks good.

172
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:09,160
I like it.

173
00:05:09,920 --> 00:05:11,040
Do you really like it?

174
00:05:11,360 --> 00:05:12,480
Of course I like it.

175
00:05:12,480 --> 00:05:13,040
Look.

176
00:05:13,200 --> 00:05:14,120
You embroidered me so thin.

177
00:05:14,120 --> 00:05:14,800
With such long legs.

178
00:05:14,800 --> 00:05:15,600
Just like the Lord.

179
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:16,640
How could I not like it?

180
00:05:18,160 --> 00:05:19,200
It's a bit rough.

181
00:05:19,640 --> 00:05:20,840
I grew up practicing martial arts.

182
00:05:20,840 --> 00:05:22,160
I've never done this before.

183
00:05:23,160 --> 00:05:24,280
I was afraid I'd make you look ugly.

184
00:05:24,840 --> 00:05:25,640
I like it.

185
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:29,080
Then why make it hard on yourself?

186
00:05:29,080 --> 00:05:30,480
Just be yourself.

187
00:05:30,840 --> 00:05:31,720
Can I?

188
00:05:31,720 --> 00:05:32,480
Of course.

189
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:33,520
Really?

190
00:05:34,720 --> 00:05:35,920
Then I want to fight you.

191
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:37,160
I grew up practicing martial arts.

192
00:05:37,160 --> 00:05:38,840
When I see an expert, I want to spar.

193
00:05:38,920 --> 00:05:39,760
I was afraid you wouldn't...

194
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:41,400
Um...

195
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:43,360
The Strategist has a bad back.

196
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:44,600
I'll help him lift a cabinet.

197
00:05:45,480 --> 00:05:46,480
Take your time embroidering.

198
00:05:54,160 --> 00:05:55,280
Brother, I'm hungry.

199
00:05:55,400 --> 00:05:56,120
Hold it.

200
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:57,480
It's all your fault.

201
00:05:57,840 --> 00:05:59,160
You even lost the knife.

202
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:09,280
Wait, let me go in first.

203
00:06:10,280 --> 00:06:10,920
Hurry up.

204
00:06:10,920 --> 00:06:12,280
Don't close it like that.

205
00:06:12,480 --> 00:06:13,160
Close the door.

206
00:06:13,280 --> 00:06:14,280
You... close it like this.

207
00:06:28,960 --> 00:06:29,720
Strategist

208
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:30,720
Thinking about something?

209
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:32,640
I am pondering.

210
00:06:32,640 --> 00:06:33,240
How can I alone

211
00:06:33,240 --> 00:06:34,960
lift such a heavy box?

212
00:06:35,080 --> 00:06:35,720
Stop thinking.

213
00:06:35,720 --> 00:06:36,480
I'll help you lift it.

214
00:06:37,640 --> 00:06:39,120
Why are you so kind to help?

215
00:06:40,440 --> 00:06:42,080
Isn't it because Miss Aqin scared you?

216
00:06:42,080 --> 00:06:43,000
She insists on fighting me.

217
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:43,880
It's so scary.

218
00:06:44,560 --> 00:06:45,880
Let me ponder this.

219
00:06:46,920 --> 00:06:48,360
Is it that you're afraid to fight her,

220
00:06:48,360 --> 00:06:49,240
or are you afraid

221
00:06:49,240 --> 00:06:50,680
your martial arts are inferior to hers?

222
00:06:51,560 --> 00:06:52,320
What do you mean?

223
00:06:52,320 --> 00:06:53,320
Literal meaning.

224
00:06:53,920 --> 00:06:55,200
What does "literal meaning" mean?

225
00:06:55,920 --> 00:06:56,520
Let's move it.

226
00:06:56,520 --> 00:06:56,960
Come on.

227
00:07:02,400 --> 00:07:03,560
You need to actually lift!

228
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:04,800
I am lifting!

229
00:07:04,920 --> 00:07:06,200
Hey, hey, you can't do it like me.

230
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:07,560
You lift, lift, lift.

231
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:08,560
Lift it up?

232
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:10,200
I am a man who excels at pondering.

233
00:07:10,200 --> 00:07:11,080
If you make me do manual labor,

234
00:07:11,080 --> 00:07:12,240
I have to use my brain, don't I?

235
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:14,800
Come, copy me.

236
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:15,600
Horse-riding stance.

237
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:18,280
Lift, lift, lift.

238
00:07:18,920 --> 00:07:19,560
Lift, lift, lift.

239
00:07:19,560 --> 00:07:20,400
Lift it up.

240
00:07:21,680 --> 00:07:22,600
Just lift like me and you're done.

241
00:07:22,600 --> 00:07:23,480
I can't take it!

242
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:30,840
Thinking again?

243
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:32,400
I am pondering.

244
00:07:32,400 --> 00:07:32,640
This...

245
00:07:32,640 --> 00:07:33,200
Stop pondering!

246
00:07:33,200 --> 00:07:33,960
Hurry and chase!

247
00:07:38,640 --> 00:07:39,240
Don't run!

248
00:07:39,880 --> 00:07:41,360
Chase! Chase!

249
00:07:43,280 --> 00:07:44,240
What is going on here?

250
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:45,680
Is the sports meet not over yet?

251
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:46,880
Can't catch up.

252
00:07:47,040 --> 00:07:48,440
Don't chase, he can't run away anyway.

253
00:07:48,880 --> 00:07:50,040
If we keep chasing, we'll have no energy left.

254
00:07:50,040 --> 00:07:51,360
We won't be able to move the cabinet later.

255
00:07:53,080 --> 00:07:54,040
Isn't that Wei Qiao?

256
00:07:55,440 --> 00:07:56,640
Free labor is here.

257
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:57,680
Back up a bit more.

258
00:07:57,920 --> 00:07:58,280
Right.

259
00:07:58,280 --> 00:07:58,960
This way, a bit more.

260
00:07:58,960 --> 00:07:59,400
This side.

261
00:07:59,520 --> 00:08:00,000
A bit more.

262
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:00,520
A bit more.

263
00:08:02,280 --> 00:08:02,600
Good.

264
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:03,080
That's enough.

265
00:08:03,280 --> 00:08:03,920
Don't move now.

266
00:08:03,920 --> 00:08:04,320
Just like that, good.

267
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:05,000
So tired.

268
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:05,640
I'm exhausted.

269
00:08:06,280 --> 00:08:07,320
Thanks for your hard work, brothers.

270
00:08:07,560 --> 00:08:08,520
I made some tea.

271
00:08:08,960 --> 00:08:09,680
Quick, have a sip.

272
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:13,920
Since Miss Yutong asks for help,

273
00:08:13,920 --> 00:08:15,480
there is no reason not to help.

274
00:08:15,880 --> 00:08:16,920
Thank you, Brother Yuwen.

275
00:08:21,680 --> 00:08:22,320
What's wrong?

276
00:08:22,800 --> 00:08:24,680
I accidentally got a big cut just now.

277
00:08:24,680 --> 00:08:26,080
It bled a lot.

278
00:08:26,600 --> 00:08:27,760
Hurry up and blow on it for him.

279
00:08:27,760 --> 00:08:29,000
Or else it'll heal right away.

280
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:30,760
Can you have some dignity?

281
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:32,000
There are two other people here!
